image


 Downton Abbey Season 4, in 1080p in x265 aka HEVC and HE-AAC 2ch audio all for about 446mb each!
 Encoded using the time consuming 2 pass, from the Blu-ray source, for the highest quality possible. 
 The Blu-ray is presented in 1080i, so I ran a decomb filter on it for better presentation on modern displays.

*Making encodes from physical blu-rays is actually harder than one would think. None of the files are labeled and I am left to figure out which file is which episode
